{"type": ["h-entry"], "properties": {"content": ["TIL that the \"-ly\" suffix commonly added to words in English to denote an adverb comes from the word \"like\" (still existing in the word \"ladylike\", for example). So \"slowly\" came from \"slow-like\" and \"carefully\" came from \"careful-like\" (possibly explaining the double \"l\")."], "mp-syndicate-to": ["twitter_bridgy_no_link"], "published": ["2020-07-03T07:32:10.377146"]}}